  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2924",
  "title": "document conditional display ",
  "body": "This comes up often (people who want to make \"autocomplete\", but with InstantSearch); you can hide the results if the query is empty like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n    container: '#hits',\r\n    templates: {\r\n      allHits: document.getElementById('hit-template').innerHTML,\r\n      empty: \"We didn't find any results for the search <em>\\\"{{query}}\\\"</em>\"\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n\r\n``` \r\n\r\n```html\r\n<script type=\"text/html\" id=\"hit-template\">\r\n  {{#query}}\r\n    {{#hits}}\r\n      <div class=\"hit\">\r\n        <div class=\"hit-image\">\r\n          <img class=\"toLowerCase\" src=\"/images/products/{{{_highlightResult.item_number.value}}}.jpg\" alt=\"{{name}}\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"hit-content\">\r\n          <h2 class=\"hit-name\"><a href=\"/product_detail.php?sku={{{_highlightResult.item_number.value}}}\" style+\"text-decoration:none; color:#333;cursor:pointer;\">{{{_highlightResult.product_name.value}}}</a></h2>\r\n          <p class=\"hit-description\">{{{_highlightResult.description.value}}}</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    {{/hits}}\r\n  {{/query}}\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Resources\r\n\r\n* [answered on Discourse](https://discourse.algolia.com/t/how-to-begin-with-no-search-results/5151/3)\r\n* helpscout: `575931335`\r\n* [slack](https://algolia.slack.com/archives/C2XP6HBKQ/p1526327403000674)",
